criteria.driver_alignment:
Discover — clearly stated decision question, metrics, discount rate and assumptions that define the analysis;  
Implement/Represent — built a year‑by‑year cash‑flow model and visualizations supporting the reflection;  
Validate — accounting checks and scenario consistency underpin the reliability of the reflections;  
Evolve — discussed staging, option value, portfolio ranking as value‑creation levers;  
Reflect — explicit recommendation, risk insight (topline sensitivity) and strategic value rationale.

Discover — student clearly frames the decision question and key financial concepts;  
Implement — student describes and delivers a reproducible script, CSV outputs, and visualizations;  
Reflect — student performs validation, sensitivity analysis, and provides a recommendation with strategic considerations.
